
Step 3: Update your database table - Make sure your orders table has these columns:

id (primary key)
user_id
batch_code
item_name
customer_name
customer_phone
customer_address
payment_status (pending/completed)
created_at (timestamp)


✅ Customer clicks button on homepage → goes to order form
✅ Customer fills batch code, item name, and info → order created as "pending"
✅ Admin sees pending orders on dashboard
✅ Admin prints invoice
✅ Admin clicks button to mark as "completed"

Step 1: Update your products table - Add a column for pictures:
ALTER TABLE `products` ADD COLUMN `image` VARCHAR(255);



Step 2: Create a Product Add page (for sellers/admins only):<?php
@include 'config.php';
session_start();

$admin_id = $_SESSION['admin_id'];

if(!isset($admin_id)){
   header('location:login.php');
}

if(isset($_POST['submit'])){
   $batch_code = $_POST['batch_code'];
   $item_name = $_POST['item_name'];
   $image = $_FILES['image']['name'];
   $image_tmp = $_FILES['image']['tmp_name'];
   $image_folder = 'uploaded_img/'.$image;

   // Move uploaded image
   move_uploaded_file($image_tmp, $image_folder);

   $insert_product = $conn->prepare("INSERT INTO `products` (batch_code, item_name, image) VALUES (?, ?, ?)");
   $insert_product->execute([$batch_code, $item_name, $image]);
   
   $message[] = 'Product added successfully!';
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
   <meta charset="UTF-8">
   <title>Add Product</title>
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/admin_style.css">
</head>
<body>

<?php include 'admin_header.php'; ?>

<section class="form-container">
   <form method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
      <h3>Add Product</h3>

      <input type="text" name="batch_code" placeholder="Batch Code" required>
      <input type="text" name="item_name" placeholder="Item Name" required>
      
      <input type="file" name="image" accept="image/*" required>
      <img id="preview" style="max-width:200px; margin-top:10px;">

      <input type="submit" name="submit" value="Add Product" class="btn">
   </form>
</section>

<script>
   // Preview image before upload
   document.querySelector('input[type="file"]').addEventListener('change', function(e){
      const reader = new FileReader();
      reader.onload = function(){
         document.getElementById('preview').src = reader.result;
      }
      reader.readAsDataURL(e.target.files[0]);
   });
</script>

</body>
</html>


